**Once upon a time, there was a rabbit and a hare who lived in a forest. The rabbit was known for his quick wit and speedy legs, while the hare was lazy and overconfident in his abilities. One day, the hare challenged the rabbit to a race. The rabbit, knowing the hare's reputation, agreed to the challenge. They decided that the finish line would be at the other end of the forest. On the day of the race, the hare sped off quickly, leaving the rabbit behind. The rabbit, however, didn't lose hope. He knew that he couldn't outrun the hare, so he came up with a clever plan. As the hare took a nap midway through the race, the rabbit quietly snuck past him and continued towards the finish line. When the hare woke up, he realized that the rabbit was already close to the finish line. With renewed energy, the hare sprinted towards the finish line. But it was too late. The rabbit had already crossed the finish line and won the race. The hare learned an important lesson that day. He realized that being lazy and overconfident would not get him anywhere. From that day forward, he worked hard to improve his skills and became a faster runner. And the rabbit continued to be known for his quick wit and cleverness. They both lived happily ever after in the forest, always striving to be their best selves.** - <@1055519550893998141> (fast)
